6\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Pi.\">Pi.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ I.\">I.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">6(5).6</biblScope></bibl>, al. : <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0019.tlg005.perseus-grc1:1270\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ar.\">Ar.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Pax\">Pax</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1270</biblScope> </bibl>-<bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0019.tlg005.perseus-grc1:1\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1</biblScope> </bibl> uses the <gramGrp opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gramGrp\"> <gram type=\"comp\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gram\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Comp.\">Comp.</a></gram> </gramGrp> in mock heroic lines.—The orig. sense was perh. <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">capable of bearing arms</tr_>; and so <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὁπλότεροι</foreign> would be <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">the serviceable men,</tr_> hence, <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">the young men,</tr_> opp. the old men and children, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:3:108\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">3.108</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg003:4:5\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Hom.</author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Epigr.\">Epigr.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">4.5</biblScope> </bibl> ; then simply, <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">younger</tr_> or <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">youngest,</tr_> hence of women, <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">Νέστορος ὁπλοτάτη θυγάτηρ</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:3:465\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Od.\">Od.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">3.465</biblScope></bibl></cit>, etc. ; then, as <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">the youngest</tr_> are <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">the last born,</tr_> <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἄνδρες ὁπλότεροι</foreign> also means <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">the latter generations, men of later days,</tr_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0005.tlg001.perseus-grc1:16:46\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Theoc.\">Theoc.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">16.46</biblScope> </bibl> ; <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ὁπλοτέρου τ᾽ Ἀχιλῆος ἀκούομεν Εὐρυλόχοιο</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0221.tlg001:80\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Euph.\">Euph.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">80</biblScope></bibl></cit>.</sense> </entryFree>"}]}